     fhir:div [ fhir:v "<div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"><p class=\"res-header-id\"><b>Generated Narrative: CodeSystem diagnosticreport-relevant-information-types</b></p><a name=\"diagnosticreport-relevant-information-types\"> </a><a name=\"hcdiagnosticreport-relevant-information-types\"> </a><p>This case-sensitive code system <code>http://hl7.org/fhir/diagnosticreport-relevant-information-types</code> defines the following codes in a Is-A hierarchy:</p><table class=\"codes\"><tr><td><b>Lvl</b></td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\"><b>Code</b></td><td><b>Display</b></td><td><b>Definition</b></td></tr><tr><td>1</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">QST<a name=\"diagnosticreport-relevant-information-types-QST\"> </a></td><td>Question</td><td>Question</td></tr><tr><td>2</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">  AOE<a name=\"diagnosticreport-relevant-information-types-AOE\"> </a></td><td>Ask at Order Entry</td><td>Ask at Order Entry</td></tr><tr><td>2</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">  ASC<a name=\"diagnosticreport-relevant-information-types-ASC\"> </a></td><td>Ask at Specimen Collection</td><td>Ask at Specimen Collection</td></tr><tr><td>1</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">RSLT<a name=\"diagnosticreport-relevant-information-types-RSLT\"> </a></td><td>Result</td><td>Result</td></tr><tr><td>2</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">  MCS<a name=\"diagnosticreport-relevant-information-types-MCS\"> </a></td><td>Micro Culture Status</td><td>Sub-type of RSLT (Result) This term identifies observations that give overall culture outcome, when no specific organism is being named.</td></tr><tr><td>2</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">  MID<a name=\"diagnosticreport-relevant-information-types-MID\"> </a></td><td>Micro Isolate Descriptor</td><td>Sub-type of RSLT (Result) This term identifies any other observations about the isolate.</td></tr><tr><td>2</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">  MIG<a name=\"diagnosticreport-relevant-information-types-MIG\"> </a></td><td>Micro Isolate Growth Quantity</td><td>Sub-type of RSLT (Result) This term identifies growth levels of an isolate – can be numeric or categorical.</td></tr><tr><td>2</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">  MIN<a name=\"diagnosticreport-relevant-information-types-MIN\"> </a></td><td>Micro Isolate Name</td><td>NSub-type of RSLT (Result) This term identifies observations that name a specific organism either at the species or the genus level.</td></tr><tr><td>2</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">  MOD<a name=\"diagnosticreport-relevant-information-types-MOD\"> </a></td><td>Micro Other Descriptor</td><td>Sub-type of RSLT (Result) This term identifies observations that do not fit the culture status, but is not at the isolate level.</td></tr><tr><td>2</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">  MSS<a name=\"diagnosticreport-relevant-information-types-MSS\"> </a></td><td>Micro Sample Stain</td><td>Sub-type of RSLT (Result) This term identifies observations on gram stains (and other stains or smears) on the clinical sample.</td></tr><tr><td>2</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">  SUP<a name=\"diagnosticreport-relevant-information-types-SUP\"> </a></td><td>Supplemental Result</td><td>Supplemental Result</td></tr><tr><td>2</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">  SUR<a name=\"diagnosticreport-relevant-information-types-SUR\"> </a></td><td>Susceptibility Related</td><td>Susceptibility Related</td></tr><tr><td>2</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">  UNSP<a name=\"diagnosticreport-relevant-information-types-UNSP\"> </a></td><td>Unspecified</td><td>Unspecified</td></tr><tr><td>1</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">SCI<a name=\"diagnosticreport-relevant-information-types-SCI\"> </a></td><td>Supporting Clinical Information</td><td>Supporting Clinical Information</td></tr><tr><td>2</td><td style=\"white-space:nowrap\">  PHX<a name=\"diagnosticreport-relevant-information-types-PHX\"> </a></td><td>Patient History</td><td>Historical patient data</td></tr></table></div>"^^rdf:XMLLiteral ]
